organizations.name: phillip plein's new york fashion week

text: Share this article Share She teamed the number with a pair of very low-key thigh-high flat boots which laced up the front and were no doubt way more comfortable than the usual heeled version she favours. Her raven locks were styled in loose curls which tumbled down past her shoulders and her make-up was dramatic with matt nude lipstick decorating her pout. Family duty: The youngest of the Kardashian-Jenner clan is also in town to support brother-in-law Kanye West who will debut his Yeezy season 5 collection in new York on Wednesday Sizzling: The curvy reality star complemented her figure in the mini dress Lacey lady: Kylie's over-the-knee stompers featured a lace-up profile Sparkling: Her ensemble had ornate pearl detail around the bodice Kylie was in excellent company on the night as she sat next to Madonna and her boyfriend, rapper Tyga on the FROW. Madonna , 58, kept covered up in a red and black coat with black fluffy trimmed hood and sunglasses. Tyga, 27, who wore a backwards baseball cap, shades and a decorated leather jacket. Side by side: Kylie Jenner and Madonna were seated together front row at Phillip Plein's New York Fashion Week show Monday night LA look: Kylie, 19, went for her usual cleavage-baring look in a white embellished mini dress with a bodice that strained to contain her breasts and lace-up thigh-high black boots Celebrity couple: The Rack City rapper showed off his diamond grill as he posed for photos with his girlfriend whose mini dress seemed one size too small for her busty body Earlier, Kylie and Tyga had paid a visit to the Keeping up With The Kardashians star's pop up store in the Soho neighborhood. Kylie posed with some of her and sister Kendall's clothing line set out on hangers underneath giant neon signs of her name. Tyga also shared a pic of the two of them on his Instagram to celebrate the venture.
